      <!-- HOW TO USE -->
      <div class="tab-panel" data-tab="howtouse">
        {%- if h contains 'niacinamide' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Cleanse thoroughly</div><p class="step-desc">Apply to completely clean, dry skin. Residual sunscreen or makeup creates a barrier that reduces how much niacinamide reaches the surface.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply 3-4 drops</div><p class="step-desc">Warm between fingertips. Press into forehead, cheeks, nose, and chin. Pressing is more effective than rubbing for serum delivery.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Wait 60 seconds</div><p class="step-desc">Niacinamide works best when it has time to penetrate before other products go on top. Sixty seconds is enough.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Moisturizer, then SPF</div><p class="step-desc">Follow with moisturizer to seal in the serum. In the morning, always finish with SPF 30 or higher.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">05</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Use twice daily</div><p class="step-desc">Morning and night gives niacinamide enough total exposure time to deliver visible results within 4 weeks.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'copper' or h contains 'peptide' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Cleanse thoroughly</div><p class="step-desc">Start with a clean, dry face. Peptides need a clear path. Anything on the surface reduces how much reaches the dermis.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply 4-5 drops</div><p class="step-desc">Warm between fingertips and press into cheeks, forehead, jawline, and neck. Pressing drives peptides deeper than rubbing does.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Wait 60 seconds</div><p class="step-desc">GHK-Cu can interact with ascorbic acid and reduce effectiveness. If you use vitamin C, apply them at different times of day.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Moisturize, then SPF in AM</div><p class="step-desc">UV exposure degrades collagen faster than any other environmental factor. Finish every morning routine with SPF 30 or higher.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'gold' or h contains 'eye' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Cleanse and dry the eye area</div><p class="step-desc">Remove all makeup and residue. Pat completely dry. Clean skin absorbs the patch actives significantly faster.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply one pair under each eye</div><p class="step-desc">Press firmly along the orbital bone. The lower curved edge sits along the cheekbone. Smooth out any air gaps.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Leave for 20 minutes</div><p class="step-desc">Keep eyes gently closed for maximum adhesion and absorption. This is the only time your phone should stay face-down.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Remove and pat in remaining serum</div><p class="step-desc">Do not rinse. Use your ring finger to gently press any remaining serum into the skin. The ring finger applies the least pressure.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'led' or h contains 'mask' or h contains 'therapy' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply to clean skin</div><p class="step-desc">Remove all makeup and sunscreen. LED penetrates more effectively through clean, unpigmented skin. Apply your serums after the session, not before.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Select your mode</div><p class="step-desc">Red (630nm) for collagen. Blue (470nm) for acne. Green (520nm) for pigmentation. Purple for scar repair. Yellow for wrinkles. Cyan for oil control. White (full spectrum) for general maintenance. Keep eyes closed throughout.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">3-minute session</div><p class="step-desc">The mask shuts off automatically. Consistency matters more than duration. Five sessions a week beats one long session every weekend.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply serums immediately after</div><p class="step-desc">LED creates a temporary increase in skin receptivity. Apply your best actives within 5 minutes of removing the mask for enhanced absorption.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'jade' or h contains 'roller' or h contains 'gua' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply serum or facial oil first</div><p class="step-desc">The jade tools need slip to glide without pulling skin. A few drops of your regular serum or facial oil works perfectly.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Start at the neck</div><p class="step-desc">Lymphatic drainage always begins at the nodes in the neck. Five to six downward strokes each side before moving to the face.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Roll outward and upward on the face</div><p class="step-desc">Always move fluid toward drainage points. Cheeks: from nose outward toward ear. Jawline: use gua sha from chin toward ear.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Under-eyes: use the small roller head</div><p class="step-desc">Very gentle pressure only. Roll from inner corner outward and down toward the cheekbone drainage node. Never pull or tug.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">05</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Clean tools after each use</div><p class="step-desc">Wipe with a damp cloth or rinse with cool water. Genuine jade is non-porous and naturally resistant to bacteria.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'cleanser' or h contains 'purity' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Wet face with lukewarm water</div><p class="step-desc">Hot water opens pores but also strips lipids. Lukewarm is the right temperature for a cleanser that's trying to protect your barrier while it cleans.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply and massage for 60 seconds</div><p class="step-desc">A pea-sized amount is enough. Work in gentle circular motions across your face and down the sides of your nose. Sixty seconds gives the CICA time to do its job.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Rinse thoroughly with cool water</div><p class="step-desc">Finish with a cool rinse to close the surface and calm any redness. Make sure no cleanser remains at the hairline or jaw, as residue is a common cause of sensitivity.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Pat dry, never rub</div><p class="step-desc">Rubbing with a towel disrupts the barrier you just cleaned. Pat dry with a clean cloth and move straight to your next step while skin is still slightly damp.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">05</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Use morning and evening</div><p class="step-desc">Gentle enough for twice-daily use. Morning cleansing removes overnight cell turnover and lets your serum absorb without anything in the way.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'revival' or h contains 'cream' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply after serums, not before</div><p class="step-desc">Creams seal in everything below them. Apply your actives first: niacinamide, peptides, or HA. Then the Revival Cream goes on last to lock it all in.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Warm a pea-sized amount</div><p class="step-desc">Rub between fingertips for 3-4 seconds. Warming the cream slightly improves spreadability and helps it melt into skin rather than sitting on top.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Press into skin, do not rub</div><p class="step-desc">Pressing drives the ceramide and CICA complex into the outer layers more effectively than rubbing. Focus on any areas that feel tight, dry, or reactive.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Extend to neck and chest</div><p class="step-desc">The skin on your neck and chest is thinner than your face and loses barrier integrity earlier. Extending the cream takes 10 extra seconds and makes a visible difference over time.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">05</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Morning: follow with SPF. Night: this is your final step.</div><p class="step-desc">At night, the Revival Cream works with your skin's overnight repair cycle. In the morning, always finish with SPF 30 or higher to protect the barrier you just rebuilt.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        {%- elsif h contains 'centella' -%}
          <div class="how-to-steps">
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Cleanse first</div><p class="step-desc">Apply to clean, slightly damp skin. The moisture helps the ampoule spread evenly and aids absorption of both Centella and niacinamide.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Apply 2–3 drops</div><p class="step-desc">Dispense and press gently into skin using your fingertips — no rubbing. Focus on areas of redness or uneven tone: cheeks, forehead, around the nose.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Wait 45–60 seconds</div><p class="step-desc">Allow the formula to absorb fully before layering anything on top. The formula is lightweight and leaves no residue.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Moisturize, then SPF in the morning</div><p class="step-desc">Follow with your moisturizer. If using in the morning, always finish with SPF — niacinamide increases photosensitivity slightly, and protecting new skin cells matters.</p></div></div>
            <div class="how-step"><div class="step-num">05</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Use morning and evening</div><p class="step-desc">Centella is non-irritating at any frequency. Most people use it twice daily from day one and notice calmer, less reactive skin within the first week.</p></div></div>
          </div>
